# Documentation

Canonical source: `documentation/` (`index.md` hub). GitHub Pages build reads `docs/` — update manifests via `scripts/materialize-docs-for-pages.sh` when moving files.

## Zero to Hero (three docs — do not conflate)

| File | Scope |
|------|-------|
| `getting-started/ZERO_TO_HERO.md` | First-lab quick start |
| `learning-path/SUPPLY_CHAIN_ATTACKS_ZERO_TO_HERO.md` | Full curriculum |
| `scenario-guides/zero-to-hero/ZERO_TO_HERO_SCENARIO_NN.md` | Per-scenario walkthrough |

Quick refs: `scenario-guides/quick-reference/QUICK_REFERENCE_SCENARIO_NN.md`. Floci track (05, 06, 14, 17, 21): `guides/FLOCI_INTEGRATION.md`.

Zero-to-hero and quick-ref trees are in `.cursorignore` for code-focused indexing — open the target file directly when editing guides.

## After content or mitigation changes

1. `scripts/lib/mitigation-playbooks.js` — canonical bullets (if mitigations changed)
2. `node scripts/sync-mitigation-gaps.js` — DETECT `## Mitigation` + README playbooks (01–06)
3. `node scripts/inject-zero-to-hero-mitigation-playbooks.js` — zero-to-hero playbooks
4. `node scripts/inject-markdown-toc.js all` — rebuild TOCs
5. Observability blocks: `detection-tools/es/scenario-diagram-steps.js` → `generate-observability-section.js`
6. `node detection-tools/es/load-runbooks.js` — if `DETECT.md` structure changed

Full script catalog: `platform/TOOLING.md`.
